node.text:
More than ever so many people are getting scammed for their Crypto so here 5 common scams you should look out for.
1.	Double Check The URLs you’re clicking on.
A lot of times scammers will create duplicate websites with similar URLs so always check the URL.

2.	Pump & Dumps.
Look out for Pump & Dumps projects if you invest at the wrong time you will get rekt.

3.	Avoid the scammers in the comment section. 
The Roaches are always spamming the comments with scams there goal is to get you to send them Crypto Dont fall for this.

4.	Impersonators
People will create fake Social media accounts imitating influecers in the space but remember no influcer in will ever ask you for money.

5.	Shady Exchanges Make sure you’re trading on reputable exanges and dont keep large amounts on any Exchange for a long period of time. Make your trades then get out!
Pro Tip
If you’re about to do something that you’re not sure about take a step back and DuckDuckgo a questions. Its likely you wasnt the first person wondering if the scam could be a scam and its likely that youd find a forum oline of people who can 

For more tips check out our 50 most common mistakes when joining crypto guide. https://cryptomaniaks.com/guides/cryptocurrency-investment-strategy-do-not-make-these-mistakes

node.title: 5 ways you can avoid Cryptocurtrency Scams
